  "response_text": "Dear [Student's Name],\n\nI was sorry to hear that you didn't pass the exam. I want you to know that I'm here to support you, and this setback doesn't define your worth or potential as a student. Everyone faces challenges, and it's completely normal to struggle with a particular subject or exam.\n\nFirstly, please take a moment to acknowledge your hard work and effort. You've put in the time and energy to prepare for this exam, and that's something to be proud of. It's okay to feel disappointed, but try not to be too hard on yourself. Instead, focus on what you can learn from this experience.\n\nLet's take a closer look at the areas where you struggled. We can work together to identify the specific topics that gave you trouble and create a plan to improve. I'm more than happy to provide additional support, whether it's extra tutoring sessions, review materials, or guidance on how to approach the subject differently.\n\nRemember that failure is an opportunity",
